d 'URVOL': module to compute Unit-root tests robust to non-stationary (time-varying) volatility
d
d     urvol implements a family of unit-root tests designed to
d remain valid, and to gain power, when the innovation variance is
d not	 constant over the sample -the "unstable" or
d "non-stationary" volatility case.  Permanent changes in variance
d (level shifts,    trends in variance, smooth transitions,
d integrated volatility) are pervasive in macroeconomic and
d financial time series    (exchange rates, interest rates, output,
d asset prices).  As Cavaliere (2004) shows, such variance dynamics
d make the standard    Dickey-Fuller (DF) and Phillips-Perron (PP)
d tests size-distorted: an early negative or late positive variance
d change can push    the empirical rejection frequency well above
d (or below) the nominal level, invalidating the usual critical
d values. 
d
d KW: volatility
d KW: nonstationary
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260709
d
d Author:   Merwan Roudane, NA
d Support: email  merwanroudane920@@gmail.com
d
f urvol.ado
f urvol.sthlp
f urvol_beare.sthlp
f urvol_bzu.sthlp
f urvol_example.do
f urvol_wbdf.sthlp
